\begin{align} \int_0^{ \frac{\pi}{2}}\! dx \: \frac{\sin x }{\sqrt{\sin 2x}} &= \frac{1}{2 \sqrt{2}} \int_0^1 dv \: v^{-3/4} (1-v)^{-1/4} \\ &= \frac{1}{2 \sqrt{2}} \Gamma \left( \frac{1}{4} \right ) \Gamma \left( \frac{3}{4} \right ) \\ &= \frac{\pi}{2} \end{align} 
